A '''bird nest''' with an egg can be found while woodcutting most types of [[tree]]s, as well as several other activities. Bird nests contain one of a red, blue, or green [[bird's egg]], and also provide an [[empty nest]]. The chance of getting a bird nest from a tree is 1/256 each time you would normally get a log, regardless of the type of tree. If a nest appears while a player is cutting a tree, a chirping sound will usually be heard, and the player will get a message in the chat box stating, "''{{Colour|#ff0000|A bird's nest falls out of the tree.}}''" The nest is dropped on the ground and will despawn after 30 seconds if not picked up. [[Redwood tree]]s do not drop egg nests, and instead only drop [[clue nest]]s.

Bird's eggs can be offered to the [[shrine]] in the [[Woodcutting Guild]] to receive 100 [[Prayer]] [[experience]] and a [[Bird nest (seeds)|seed nest]].

When [[woodcutting]], a roll is done to determine the type of nest the player will receive. The table contains 100 slots: 3/100 egg nest (one for each colour), 32/100 [[Bird nest (ring)|ring nest]], 65/100 [[Bird nest (seeds)|seed nest]]. When wearing a [[strung rabbit foot]], five seed slots are removed, making the chances 3/95 for bird's egg, 32/95 for ring and 60/95 for seeds.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1055815273763217414|date=26 October 2018|archiveurl=https://archive.is/B74zS|archivedate=26 May 2020|quote=If you've got the rabbit foot necklace, pick number 0-94 inclusive. Otherwise, pick number 0-99 inclusive. 0 = red egg, 1 = blue egg, 2 = green egg, 3-34 = ring, otherwise it's seeds.}}

During [[bird house trapping]], up to 10 nest rolls are performed with a chance of getting a ring nest. For successful rolls, the chance is 3/100 for an egg nest. Wearing a strung rabbit foot removes 5 empty nest slots, making the chance for an egg nest 3/95.

Egg nests are also rewarded from [[Managing Miscellania]] when subjects are tasked with collecting maple, teak or mahogany logs.

